<p>Suppose I have two classes like:</p>  <pre><code>class Abc   def initialize(arg1, arg2)     @a = arg1     @b = arg2   end    def sum     return @a+@b   end end  obj = Abc.new(2, 3) obj.add # =&gt; 5 </code></pre>  <p>or </p>  <pre><code>class Abc1   def sum(arg1, arg2)     return arg1+arg2   end end  obj = Abc1.new obj.sum(2,3) # =&gt;5 </code></pre>  <p>In both classes, I call a <code>sum</code> method and get <code>5</code> as the result. Which approach is better and why?</p>